# General Code Style & Formatting
- Use english for code and comments.
- Follow the Airbnb Style Guide for code formatting.
- Use KebabCase for React component file names (e.g.user-card.tsx, not UserCard.tsx).
- Prefer named exports for components.
- Use TypeScript for type safety.

# Project Structure & Architecture
- Follow Next.js patterns and use the App Router.
- Use Server Components for most of the code and wrap user specific code in client components or Suspense boundary.
- Use PPR for prefetching.

# Styling & UI
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling.
- Use Shadcn UI for components.

# Data Fetching & Forms
- Use Supabase for data fetching and authentication.
- Use supabase cache helpers with Tanstack Query for data fetching and mutations in client side. I write a PrefetchWrapper component to handle prefetching in server side.
- Use React Hook Form for form handling.
- Use Zod for validation.

# State Management & Logic
- Use React Context for state management.
- Use jotai for state management in client side.

# Backend & Database
- Use Supabase for database access.